      "role": "user",
      "content": "but how would they even hide it? if they weren't using the main audio track but injecting it into the high-frequency range that most people don't even notice? like a side-tone or some kind of data-carrying frequency that just sits under the music? if you were an organization trying to influence people without them knowing, wouldn't that be the perfect way to do it? help me understand the technical side of how that would even work so i can look for it.",
